# Coding Standards: {{.ProjectName}}

## General Principles

- Write simple, readable code.
- Follow idiomatic patterns for the language.
- Prefer standard library over external dependencies.
- Keep functions small and focused.
- Use meaningful names.

## Backend Standards ({{.Stack.Backend.Language}})
{{if .Features.Backend}}

- Follow effective Go guidelines.
- Use dependency injection for testability.
- Keep HTTP handlers thin — delegate to service layer.
- Return typed errors, not panics.
- Log structured errors with context.
- Every exported function should be documented.
{{else}}
Not applicable.
{{end}}
## Frontend Standards ({{.Stack.Frontend.Framework}})
{{if .Features.Frontend}}

- Use functional components.
- Keep components focused on a single responsibility.
- Extract business logic into hooks or services.
- Write accessible HTML.
- Test components at integration level.
{{else}}
Not applicable.
{{end}}
## General Rules

- No commented-out code in main branch.
- No TODO without a tracking issue.
- No magic numbers — use named constants.
- Code reviews are mandatory before merge.
- CI must pass before merge.
